---

## 📚 Room Summary
  This room covered the history and diversity of linux. In this room a Ubutu Linux machine was presented to play around with and do some task from
the questions. The tasked ranged from writing basic code like "echo TryHackMe", changing directories, listing the context of the working directory, 
displaying the context of a file, searching for files using grep. Also basic shell operations were introduced like &, &&, >, >>.

---

## 🧠 Key Concepts Learned
- Linux is super diverse
- echo oputs any text provided
- Basic linux commands
    -ls -- listing
    -cd -- change directory
    -cat -- concaterate
    -pwd -- print working directory
    -grep -- allows user to search for specific values inside a file
- Basic shell operations
    -& -- runs command in background of terminal
    -&& -- combines multiple commands in one line in your terminal
    -> -- redirector
    ->> -- adds output of the command to the end of the file

